OL,3,CThe Abbeystead survivor raising money
OL,4,Cin memory of those he lost forty years
OL,5,Cago
OL,7,FJohn said: "It was like a will-o'-the-
OL,8,Fwisp type of flame that engulfed us
OL,9,Fall. It blew the roof off the
OL,10,Fbuilding, and it actually went up and
OL,11,Fdown onto the people. Then when it
OL,12,Fwent into the ground some people fell
OL,13,Finto the water. It was horrendous."
OL,15,FJohn was left with serious burns and
OL,16,Freceived urgent treatment at the Royal
OL,17,FPreston Hospital's burn unit.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
